      <section eId="sec_CC-137">
        <num>CC 137</num>
        <heading>137.  Denial of visitation; sex offense; death of a parent</heading>
        <subsection eId="CC-137__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>In a proceeding in which visitation of a child is being sought by a parent, if the
child was conceived through the commission of a sex offense as provided by R.S. 15:541,
the parent who committed the sex offense shall be denied visitation rights and contact with
the child.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CC-137__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>In a proceeding in which visitation of a child is being sought by a relative by
blood or affinity, if the court determines, by a preponderance of the evidence, that the
intentional criminal conduct of the relative resulted in the death of the parent of the child, the
relative shall be denied visitation rights and contact with the child.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=108726</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
